Kern Licensing Overview

Kern uses a split licensing model.

The core toolchain is licensed under the GNU General Public License version 3
or later. This covers:

- compiler/
- tools/craft/
- tools/lsp/
- tools/kernworker/

The user-facing libraries, installer, shared helper crates, examples, editor
extension, documentation, package templates, and other repository material are
licensed under the MIT License unless a file or package says otherwise.

The full license texts are available in:

- LICENSES/GPL-3.0-or-later.txt
- LICENSES/MIT.txt

See docs/licensing.md for the maintained licensing policy and package
boundaries.
